'''Takekumateru no Mikoto''' (健隈照命, birth and death dates unknown) was a [[Kofun period]] noble and a notable leader of the '''{{ill|Suwa no Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|洲羽国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa no Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=|1=Suwa-no-kokuzo|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q67499361}}'''. He is also known by the name '''Takekumateru no Mikoto'''. == See Also == * [[:en:Kuni no miyatsuko|Kuni no Miyatsuko]] * [[:en:Suwa-taisha|Suwa-taisha]] * [[:en:Shinano Province|Shinano Province]] * {{ill|Suwa Province|ja|諏訪国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Province|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 諏方国|1=Suwa Province|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1192248}} * {{ill|Yagata no Sukune no Kami|ja|八縣宿禰神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yagata no Sukune no Kami|qq=}} * {{ill|Takeminawake no Mikoto|ja|武美名別命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminawake no Mikoto|qq=}} * {{ill|Takakuni no Hikono Mikoto|ja|武国彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takakuni no Hikono Mikoto|qq=}} * {{ill|List of figures before the Asuka period|ja|飛鳥時代以前の人物一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of figures before the Asuka period|qq=|1=List of ancient Japanese figures|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11665973}}
